column4:
1. Server
Requires Node.js 20 LTS and npm.
Supports running backend, frontend, and admin via:
npm run dev (all services)
npm run server --prefix backend (backend only)
2. Database
Uses MongoDB (Atlas or local).
Must configure MONGO_URL in backend/.env.
.env also requires credentials for VNPAY / Stripe / MoMo.
3. Web Browser
Modern browser needed to access:
Frontend UI: http://localhost:5173
Admin Dashboard: http://localhost:5174

column5: Allows registered users to access the system by providing valid login credentials (account name and password)
column6: The user must already have a registered account.The user must provide correct login credentials.

column5: Creates a new user account by collecting required user information such as name, email/phone, and password

column5: Displays the list of available food items, including names, prices, descriptions, and images if applicable
column6: The system must have an internet/database connection to fetch menu data.

column5: Adds a selected menu item to the user’s cart with a specified quantity.
column6: The user must be logged in.The selected menu item must exist and be available.The quantity must be greater than zero.

column5: Modifies the quantity of an item in the user’s cart.
column6: The user must be logged in.The item must already exist in the cart.The updated quantity must be valid (e.g., quantity > 0).

column5: Removes a specific item from the user’s cart.
column6: The user must be logged in.The item must already be present in the cart.

column5: Retrieves and displays all items currently stored in the user’s cart, including quantities and total price.
column6: The user must be logged in.The user must have an active cart (even if it is empty).

column5: Creates an order from the user’s cart, confirms order details, and sends the order for processing.
column6: The user must be logged in.The cart must contain at least one item.A payment method and delivery/pickup details must be provided (if required).All menu items in the cart must still be available.

column5: Automatically selects the nearest branch using browser geolocation and applies it to customer experience (menu/order).
column6: User opens Home for the first time or has no preferred branch saved; browser supports geolocation.

column5: Allows the user to manually select a branch when geolocation is denied, unavailable, or fails.
column6: Geolocation is denied/unavailable; active branches exist in the system.

column5: Persists the selected branch as the preferred branch in StoreContext for future sessions.
column6: User has selected a valid branch.

column5: Displays the menu correctly according to the selected branch (no cross-branch data leakage).
column6: A branch is selected; menu v2 backend is available.

column5: Searches menu items by keyword and returns matching results; handles “no result” properly.
column6: Menu data for the selected branch is loaded; user is on Menu page.

column5: Filters menu items by category and displays the correct subset.
column6: Categories exist; menu for the selected branch is loaded.

column3: View item detail and choose variant
column5: Displays item details and allows selecting a valid variant before adding to cart.
column6: An item with at least one variant exists; menu is loaded.

column3: Change branch while cart has items
column5: Handles cart conflicts when switching branches (clear cart, keep cart, or warn user according to business rule).
column6: Cart contains at least one item; user attempts to change branch.

column5: Validates required fields on PlaceOrder (address/receiver info/delivery method if applicable) and blocks submission when missing/invalid.
column6: User is logged in; cart has valid items; user is on PlaceOrder page.

column3: PlaceOrder with out-of-stock or disabled item
column5: Prevents ordering or shows clear error when cart contains out-of-stock or disabled variants at checkout time.

column5: Allows selecting a payment gateway (VNPAY/Stripe/MoMo) and proceeds with payment initiation.

column5: Completes payment successfully and updates payment status; redirects to Verify and reflects correct status in MyOrders.
column6: Sandbox/mock payment success is available; order exists.

column5: Handles payment failure/cancel; Verify shows correct failure/cancel status and does not mark payment as success.
column6: Sandbox/mock payment failure/cancel is available; order exists.

column5: Verify page reads payment return data and syncs with backend to update order/payment status correctly.
column6: OrderId/return parameters exist; backend verify endpoint is available.

column5: Refreshing or revisiting Verify does not create duplicate payments/orders and does not corrupt final status.
column6: An order has a completed or failed payment attempt; Verify link can be accessed again.

column5: Displays the logged-in user’s order list correctly (and pagination if any).
column6: User is logged in and has at least one order.

column5: Displays order detail accurately (items, branch, payment status, delivery status).
column6: User is logged in; the order belongs to the user.

column5: Shows order status updates correctly over time; prevents invalid “status jumping” presentation.
column6: Admin updates order status; user checks MyOrders.

column5: Allows user to cancel an order only in allowed statuses; updates order status accordingly.
column6: User is logged in; order is in a cancellable status; user is the order owner.

column5: Allows user to confirm receipt when eligible; updates final order status accordingly.

column5: Updates user profile information and displays updated data correctly.
column6: User is logged in.

column5: Uploads avatar successfully; validates file type/size and displays new avatar.
column6: User is logged in; avatar upload API is available.

column5: Logs out and clears token, cart, and preferred branch stored in StoreContext/local storage.
column6: User is logged in.

column6: User has an expired/invalid token; attempts to access protected pages (e.g., MyOrders) or APIs.
